This paper is about open-domain dialog systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a neural dialog model, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) the second likely sub-category. The paper also compares its proposed model with two baseline models, which involves statistical analysis and machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) the third likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on generating emotionally appropriate responses, which involves human-computer interaction, making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) the fourth likely sub-category. Finally, the paper also involves social dynamics and communication, making cs.SD (Social and Information Networks) the fifth likely sub-category.
